ENTRY            A1161   20260211   20260508   20260508       A132
SUBENT        A1161001   20260211   20260508   20260508       A132
BIB                 13         28
TITLE      3H(p,gamma)4He reaction below Ep = 3.0 MeV
AUTHOR     (R.C.McBroom,H.R.Weller,N.R.Roberson,D.R.Tilley)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,25,1644,1982)
INSTITUTE  (1USATNL,1USAFLA,1USADKE,1USANCA)
FACILITY   (CYGFF,1USATNL) The proton beam in the energy range
           of 17 -30 MeV was obtained from the Triangle Univ.
           Nucl. Lab. (TUNL) Cyclo-Graaff facility.
           The TUNL FN Tandem provided the proton beam
           below 17 MeV.
SAMPLE     Tritium target thickness of 0.13+-0.02 mg/cm2
METHOD     (TOF)
DETECTOR   (NAICR) 25.4cm x 25.4cm NaI detector surrounded by a
           plastic anticoincidence shield.
MONITOR    (1-H-3(P,EL)1-H-3,,DA)
MONIT-REF  (A1022001,J.E.Brolley Jr+,J,PR,117,1307,1960)
           (A1017001,J.L.Detch+,J,PR/C,4,52,1971)
STATUS     (SPSDD,C0111001) The cross section data are superseded
            by data from C0111.
COMMENT    Author's comment from (PR/C,42,R1167,1990):
            'Unfortunately it is not possible to determine with
           certainty a specific flaw in this work. Target
           nonuniformities and the tight geometry of the solid-
           state detectors in the capture target chamber seem to
           be the most likely sources of error.'
HISTORY    (19840215C) Compilation produced by Arzamas RFNC-VNIIEF
           (19990220U)CNPD: corrected 4-dig. year and lower cases.
           (20090929A).Correction in sub002-005-by CAJAD
           (20260211U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              28
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           31
